akland, California]]\n|\n|piano\n|}\n\n----\n<small>Without recording date - To be inserted in the list</small>\n*[[J\u00f6rg Demus]] - mid-1950s - Westminster WL 5241 - ''piano''\n*[[Ito Ema]]<ref>Billed as the premier audiophile recording of the Variations, recorded with handmade microphones and independent circuitry for simultaneous digital and analog recordings.</ref> - MA Recordings M024A\n*[[Zuzana R\u016f\u017ei\u010dkov\u00e1]] - Erato \u2013 ERA 9034 - Neupert (Mercier-Ythier) ''harpsichord''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n{{Compositions for Organ, Keyboard and Lute by Johann Sebastian Bach}}\n[[Category:Discographies of compositions by J. S. Bach]]\n", "text_old": "{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Goldberg Variations'' discography}}\n\nThis is a partial list of commercial or professional recordings of [[Johann Sebastian Bach]]'s ''[[Goldberg Variations]]'', organized chronologically.  You can alphabetically sort each column by clicking on the small box at the top of that column (click again to sort reverse-alphabetically).\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Artist\n!Date\n!Place\n!Recording\n!Instrument and repeats\n|-\n| [[Rudolf Serkin|Serkin, Rudolf]] || circa 1928 || [[Stuttgart]] || Welte piano rolls || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Wanda Landowska|Landowska, Wanda]] || November 1933 || [[Paris]] || EMI 5 6720 ADD || ''harpsichord''\n|-\n| [[Claudio Arrau|Arrau, Claudio]] || January\u2013March 1942 || || RCA CD GD 87841 || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Wanda Landowska|Landowska, Wanda]] || 1945 || New York City || RCA || ''harpsichord''\n|-\n| [[Rosalyn Tureck|Tureck, Rosalyn]] || 1947 || || mono Allegro / Everest || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Ralph Kirkpatrick|Kirkpatrick, Ralph]] || 1952 || || mono Haydn Society || ''harpsichord''\n|-\n| [[Gustav Leonhardt|Leonhardt, Gustav]] || 1953 || [[Vienna]] || stereo Vanguard (the first of three recordings by this artist) || ''harpsichord'' \n|-\n| [[Isolde Ahlgrimm|Ahlgrimm, Isolde]] || January 1954 || [[Vienna]] || Philips, mono || Ammer ''harp