and, Robin]] || 1996 ||  || d'Note Classics DND 1013- ADD || ''piano'' ''All repeats''\n|-\n| [[Masaaki Suzuki|Suzuki, Masaaki]] || February, June and July 1997 || || [[BIS (record label)|BIS]] BIS-CD-310819 DDD || ''harpsichord'' ''All repeats''\n|-\n| [[J\u00f3zsef E\u00f6tv\u00f6s (musician)|E\u00f6tv\u00f6s, J\u00f3zsef]] || 1997 ||  || EJ-01WZ DDD || ''solo guitar''\n|-\n| [[Michal Ma\u0161ek|Ma\u0161ek, Michal]] || 1997 ||  || LT 0056-2 131 || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Shelley Katz|Katz, Shelley]] || 18\u201319 November 1997 || Snape Maltings Concert Hall || Private Label - Produced by Erik Smith with fewer than 30 edits to the entire master || ''piano'' all repeats except for minor variations\n|-\n| [[Ivo Janssen]] || Februari 1998 || || Void || ''piano'' \n|-\n| [[Rosalyn Tureck|Tureck, Rosalyn]] || March 1998 || [[Hamburg]] || 2 CD DG (the seventh and last recording of the Goldbergs by this artist) ||  ''Piano''\n|-\n| [[Andrei Vieru|Vieru, Andrei]] || 1998 || || Harmonia Mundi 901666 || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Abram Bezuijen|Bezuijen, Abram]] || 1998 || || VLS Records VLC 0598 || ''organ''\n|-\n| [[Zhu Xiao-Mei|Zhu, Xiao-Mei]] || 1999 || || Mandala Records DDD || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Canadian Brass]] || 1999 || || RCA Red Seal DDD (Echo Award 2002) || ''brass quintet''\n|-\n| [[Evgeni Koroliov|Koroliov, Evgeni]] || 1999 || Festeburgkirche, Frankfurt am Main, Germany || H\u00e4nssler || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Pieter-Jan Belder|Belder, Pieter-Jan]] || 20 April, 8/9 July 1999 || || Brilliant Classics 92284 DDD || ''harpsichord''\n|-\n| [[Angela Hewitt|Hewitt, Angela]] || 28 August-1 September 1999 || Henry Wood Hall, London || Hyperion Records CDA 67305 || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Ragna Schirmer|Schirmer, Ragna]] || June 1999 || Johanniterkirche, Gro\u00df Eichsen, Germany || Berlin Classics 001716 DDD || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Les Violons du Roy]] || September 1999 ||  Saint-Ir\u00e9n\u00e9e, Qu\u00e9bec, Canada  || 1 CD Dorian ||''transcription for string orchestra''\n|-\n| [[Amati St