r two clarinets and cello; and, [[:File:J.S.Bach-Goldberg variation 19.ogg|\"Variatio 21 Canone alla Settima\"]] is arranged for two clarinets and bass.</ref><ref>[http://www-acad.sheridanc.on.ca/~degazio/AboutMeFolder/MusicPages/musicperf.html Bruno Degazio, Sheridan College, Music Performances] (accessed July 28, 2015).</ref>\n|-\n| [[Jory Vinikour|Vinikour, Jory]] || 2001 || [[San Raphael, CA]] || Delos Records || ''harpsichord'' ''All repeats''\n|-\n| [[Wolfgang Dimetrik|Dimetrik, Wolfgang]] || 2001 ||  || Amphion records 20126 DDD || ''accordion''\n|-\n| [[Francesco Tristano Schlim\u00e9|Schlim\u00e9, Francesco Tristano]] || 2001 || || Accord ACD 098 with [[BWV]] 622 || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Ramin Bahrami|Bahrami, Ramin]] || February 2002 || La Chaux-de-Fonds (CH) || Decca 476 282 DDD || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Andr\u00e1s Schiff|Schiff, Andr\u00e1s]] || October 2002 || [[Basel]] || ECM DDD (his second recording; made live in concert) || ''piano'' \n|-\n| [[Ketil Haugsand|Haugsand, Ketil]] || 2002 || || [[Simax]] PSC 1192 || ''harpsichord''\n|-\n| [[Christina Bj\u00f8rk\u00f8e|Bj\u00f8rk\u00f8e, Christina]] || 2002 || Scandinavian Classics 220590 -205 DDD || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Jill Crossland|Crossland, Jill]] || 2003 || || Apex (Warner Classics) 0927 49979 2 DDD || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Pierre Hanta\u00ef|Hanta\u00ef, Pierre]] || 2003 || || Mirare MIR 9945 DDD (his second recording) || ''harpsichord'' \n|-\n| [[Martin Stadtfeld|Stadtfeld, Martin]] || March 2004 || || Sony BMG SK93101 DDD || ''piano''\n|-\n| [[Mika V\u00e4yrynen (musician)|V\u00e4yrynen, Mika]] || 2004 || || ALBA ABCD 191 || ''accordion''\n|-\n| [[Catherine Ennis|Ennis, Catherine]] || 2004 || || Mollterz || ''organ''\n|-\n| [[Jacqueline Ogeil|Ogeil, Jacqueline]] || 2004 || || ABC Classics - Discovery 476 3529 || ''harpsichord''\n|-\n| [[Trio Zilliacus Persson Raitinen|Raitinen, Trio Zilliacus Persson]]<ref>Won a Swedish [[Grammis]] in the Classical Ensemble of the Year-category in 2004.</ref> || 2004 || ||